title: For Trade:  Super-Super rare Bad-Ass Race-Ready BMX for Trade.
postcontent:
Are you gearing up for the upcoming BMX racing season???? Does your son or daughter need a bike that will get them over the finish line first??? Have they out grown their Mini and are ready for a full-size jammer??? Or maybe you want one to tool around the track on while they race- or you can race it- (I'm 6'2 and it fits me perfectly but also fits my buddy who is 5 foot...) Or how 'bout a bike that other's will go, "Dude... where'd you get THAT bike!?!?!?"

Then this is it.... Complete Custom Build. Every part was ordered al-a-carte. I spent over $1000 plus time and labor putting this bike together 15 years ago.  At the time, Aluminum Frames and Forks were unheard of... now everybody makes them, but nobody made them like this...

This is one of the Rarest BMX bikes EVER made.

Made by the Profile 3-piece crank company and not many were made... it's so rare that you can't even Google it and find out anything about it. Super Rare!

The details:
Make: Rocket - Frame and Forks
Model: Apollo Pro XL
Materials: 6160 Aluminum Frame, Fork, Goose-Neck, Rims, Hubs, Spockets, ect...
Handle Bars: PowerLite "Power Bars" (Power bends at the grips) Chrome-Molly
Grips: Ame "pyramids"
Headset: PowerLite  Aluminum w/ Aheadset bearings and Head Lock (super tight)
Brakes: Shimano  XTR "V" Brakes- Best Brakes Ever Made!
Brake Lever: Shimano XTR "two-finger, 3-position" 
Seat: Bontrager R Racing series
Seat Post: GT Aluminum
Seat Post Clamp: Haro Aluminum Quick Release
Cranks: Poverty Chrome 180mm  Chrome-Molly-  Longest cranks available
Pedals: GT Aluminum w/ removable-replaceable gripping-studs
Front Sprocket: Profile  47 tooth  Aluminum - Largest sprocket available
Rear Sprocket: Profile  16 tooth Aluminum  (14 tooth not available at the time of build)
Rims: Mavic w/ S.U.P sealed hubs with UB control  (made in France)
Tires: Odyssey Bermudas "snake-bellies" (Will need to change to Knobbies for dirt track)

All bearings from the headset to the cranks to the hubs are sealed. Bike has never been left outside, abused, or crashed. Rides like a Cadillac and with the long cranks and large front sprocket, one rotation equals one and a half rotations on a average race bike... this is one bad scooter!

title: For Sale/Trade:  Calico M-100 .22 lr
postcontent:
This thing might be one of the most fun rifles I have ever owned... But I know prices for these things are high, and I need to be practical- I have no long range rifle, and I should.

I am mostly looking for a trade- Something long range.

I have TWO-  ONE HUNDRED  round magazines- I never shot through the second magazine-  I think the second one just needs a follower put in it- Which is a relatively cheap part 

Rifle is used- I'm nost sure how many rounds have been through it, it's been years since I have fired it, but as I recall this thing works good,  Again, I hate to see it go, but I need to be practical instead of just looking at the fun factor. The photo is just a stock photo. I do not know the round count- I bought it used,  I don't remember how many rounds I have fired. You are very welcome to meet me at the range and try it before trading though:)

Disclaimer
It's a shame I have to say this-
But- Some people seem to think very highly of the fact that they can come up with cash today... As if that takes some type of Super Human Feet that instantaniously cuts the price by a large amount......

So PLEASE- if you don't want me to laugh at your offer- Don't say things like "I'll give you $500 cash money today!"....

There are just so many things I could mock about such a statement...

It's as if such a person thinks by adding the words "cash money" it makes his offer better...
because afterall in his mind "cash money" is twice as good as simply saying cash... or just saying money...

His offer is Cash money... His "cash money" spends much better than ordinary cash...

Or how about this genius- What other things do you think you are going to pay with other than cash? What else could you be offering? Teddy Bears? Food Stamps? Snowballs? Kittens? A Check perhaps? Who in their right mind is going to meet a total stranger and take a check and let the stranger walk away with an expensive rifle????

So when making an offer all you have to do is say the amount, it is a given that you are offering cash...

Again I am sorry I had to waste those 60 seconds of your life reading this, but the type of folk who use that kind of verbage are usually lowballers anyway, and I don't mind offending those types.  

Thanks and have a great day:)

- Ruger Cleaning Cloth 
- Ruger Pad Lock
- Trigger Lock 
- (2) Extended magazine floor plates 
- (2) Magazines 

The SR22 has light double-action and crisp single-action trigger pulls. Its external hammer is designed with a rounded spur for easy cocking and single-action shooting. The SR22 features a polymer frame and two interchangeable (no tools required) rubberized grips with angled serrations, allowing shooters to select either a slim or wider palm swell option. The aerospace-grade aluminum slide has serrations on both front and rear for better grip and slide manipulation. The easy-to-use underside Picatinny rail features multiple cross slots for variable mounting of most popular accessories. 

The 3-dot sight system has a fixed front sight and a rear sight that is adjustable for both windage and elevation. A reversible blade allows shooters to select two white dots or a solid black blade. Other SR22 features include a stainless steel replaceable barrel, an ambidextrous manual thumb safety/decocking lever, ambidextrous magazine release, plus a visual inspection port to determine the load status of the pistol. The SR22 includes two finger grip extension floorplates that can be added to the magazine for comfort and grip. 

Comes with original box, paper work, spent round from Ruger, all the odds and ends you get when you purchase a firearm new. This is a great gun for any shooter and is ready to see some rounds down range.
